feat: switch system currency from SAR to PKR; reduce payments to Cash + Credit Card

User: "prices should be in PKR (Rupees) throughout the system and also
for payment only cash and credit card is fine"

Currency
--------
We store money as integer minor-units (1 PKR = 100 paisa); math is
unchanged because the old halalas/SAR was also 1/100. Display flips
everywhere from "X.XX SAR" to "Rs N" with thousand separators and no
decimals (PKR is consumer-priced in whole rupees).

- apps/{mobile,web,admin,pos}/src/lib/format.ts: fmtSAR now outputs
  "Rs 1,234". Kept named fmtSAR to avoid touching 30+ call sites.
- apps/api/src/shared/utils/halalas.ts: formatSAR likewise outputs PKR.
  Type Halalas + sarToHalalas/halalasToSar kept (math identical).
- apps/api/src/shared/utils/halalas.test.ts: assertions updated.
- apps/api/src/modules/payments/payment.model.ts: currency default PKR.
- apps/api/src/modules/payments/payments.service.ts: currency PKR.
- apps/api/src/modules/payments/gateways/gateway.interface.ts: literal
  type 'PKR'.

Seed + migration
----------------
- apps/api/src/scripts/seed.ts: every price multiplied by 30 to give
  realistic PKR amounts (classic pizza Rs 1,050, cheeseburger Rs 840,
  fries Rs 270). Address country PK, phones +92.
- apps/api/src/scripts/migrate-to-pkr.ts: NEW one-off, idempotent
  script that multiplies Product.basePrice + size/crust deltas,
  Topping.basePrice, Order.pricing.* and items unitPrice/lineTotal/
  modifier prices, Payment.amount + refunds amounts by 30 in-place,
  then flips Payment.currency to PKR. A Meta doc prevents re-runs.
- apps/api/package.json: npm run migrate-to-pkr script.

Hardcoded SAR strings / KSA locale -> PKR / PK locale
-----------------------------------------------------
- Mobile: home offer Rs 2,400, delivery >Rs 2,000, checkout
  Delivery Rs 250, loyalty "1 point per rupee" / "100 pts = Rs 1".
- Web: PromoStrip thresholds, HeroCarousel delivery threshold,
  homepage offer cards, checkout delivery.
- Admin: Dashboard Karachi tz + tooltip Rs N, Reports tooltip,
  Products label "Base price (PKR)".
- POS Sales: collapsed to Cash + Credit Card; types narrowed; card
  button posts method visa.
- KDS: header clock Asia/Karachi.
- Web account: timestamp Asia/Karachi.
- API reports: dayBounds anchored to +05:00; grouping tz Asia/Karachi.
- API branches.service.ts: order-number rollover Asia/Karachi.
- API phone.ts: anchor prefix changed +966 -> +92.

Payment methods reduced
-----------------------
- Mobile checkout PAY: { cash, visa } (visa labeled Credit Card).
- Web checkout PAY_METHODS: same two; removed Smartphone/Wallet
  imports.
- POS Sales: card button posts visa (was mada); paying-state type
  narrowed.

The API Payment.method enum still accepts the full historical list
so any legacy data keeps validating; only the UI surface is restricted.

Login defaults (cosmetic)
-------------------------
Seeded login forms now pre-fill +923000000001/02/03 to match the new
seed phone numbers; fields remain editable.

Notes
-----
- VAT rate left at 15%. If you want Pakistan GST (17/18%) say the word.
- Loyalty math unchanged. After migration, 100 pts redeems Rs 1 -- quite
  weak as a percentage. Tune separately if you want it stronger.
- migrate-to-pkr is a multiplicative re-scale (x30), NOT a real FX
  conversion -- it exists to make a SAR-seeded dev DB look like PKR.
